    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h4 id="How-to-bind-domain-name-to-github-page"><a href="#How-to-bind-domain-name-to-github-page" class="headerlink" title="How to bind domain name to github page"></a>How to bind domain name to github page</h4><p>When using github and hexo to deploy our own blog, we may want to customize our domain instead of using “name.github.io”, We can bind a domain name to it.</p><a id="more"></a><h5 id="1-Domain-name"><a href="#1-Domain-name" class="headerlink" title="1. Domain name"></a>1. Domain name</h5><p>Get a domain name, and resolve it to your “name.github.io”.</p><h5 id="2-Github"><a href="#2-Github" class="headerlink" title="2. Github"></a>2. Github</h5><p>Add a file named CNAME in blog_name/source/, then write your domain name into it(without https, or www).</p>]]></content>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;h4 id=&quot;How-to-bind-domain-name-to-github-page&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#How-to-bind-domain-name-to-github-page&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;How to bind domain name to github page&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;How to bind domain name to github page&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;When using github and hexo to deploy our own blog, we may want to customize our domain instead of using “name.github.io”, We can bind a domain name to it.&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
