    <category term="git" scheme="https://dtover.github.io/tags/git/"/>
    
  </entry>
  
  <entry>
    <title>ZSH Control key bindings</title>
    <link href="https://dtover.github.io/2020/04/19/ZSH-Control-key-bindings/"/>
    <id>https://dtover.github.io/2020/04/19/ZSH-Control-key-bindings/</id>
    <published>2020-04-19T08:03:07.000Z</published>
    <updated>2020-09-01T12:10:01.311Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="Useful-ZSH-Key-Bindings"><a href="#Useful-ZSH-Key-Bindings" class="headerlink" title="Useful ZSH Key Bindings"></a>Useful ZSH Key Bindings</h3><p><em>In order to use these key bindings more comfortably, it is a good choice to switch the L_Control and L_ALT</em></p><blockquote><ol><li>Ctrl + u : clear the current line</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="2"><li>Ctrl + a : move to the start of the line</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="3"><li>Ctrl + e : move to the end of the line or complete the command according to the history</li></ol></blockquote><a id="more"></a><blockquote><ol start="4"><li>Ctrl + f : move to the next char or complete the command according to the history</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="5"><li>Ctrl + b : move to the previous char</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="6"><li>Ctrl + p : fill with previous command in history</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="7"><li>Ctrl + n : fill with next command in history</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="8"><li>Ctrl + r : search the history command</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="9"><li>Ctrl + y : paste the command</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="10"><li>Ctrl + h : delete the char before the cursor</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="11"><li>Ctrl + d : If the cursor is on a char, it will delete this char. If not, it will list the possible options that you may input</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="12"><li>Ctrl + w : delete the word before the cursor </li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="13"><li>Ctrl + k : delete from the cursor to end of the line</li></ol></blockquote><blockquote><ol start="14"><li>Ctrl + t : swap the two char before the cursor </li></ol></blockquote>]]></content>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;h3 id=&quot;Useful-ZSH-Key-Bindings&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Useful-ZSH-Key-Bindings&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Useful ZSH Key Bindings&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Useful ZSH Key Bindings&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In order to use these key bindings more comfortably, it is a good choice to switch the L_Control and L_ALT&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ctrl + u : clear the current line&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol start=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ctrl + a : move to the start of the line&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol start=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ctrl + e : move to the end of the line or complete the command according to the history&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
